tokens.t: I have kept thy precepts and thy testimonies: for all my ways
before thee.

verses.plain: Let my cry come near before thee, O LORD: give me understanding according to thy word.

tokens.t: Let my cry come near before thee, O
: give me understanding according to thy word.

verses.plain: Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.

tokens.t: Let my supplication come before thee: deliver me according to thy word.

verses.plain: My lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.

tokens.t: My lips shall utter praise, when thou hast taught me thy statutes.

verses.plain: My tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments are righteousness.

tokens.t: My tongue shall speak of thy word: for all thy commandments
righteousness.

verses.plain: Let thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.

tokens.t: Let thine hand help me; for I have chosen thy precepts.

verses.plain: I have longed for thy salvation, O LORD; and thy law is my delight.

tokens.t: I have longed for thy salvation, O
; and thy law
my delight.

verses.plain: Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.

tokens.t: Let my soul live, and it shall praise thee; and let thy judgments help me.

verses.plain: I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.

tokens.t: I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek thy servant; for I do not forget thy commandments.

footnotes.text: thy: Heb. judgments of thy righteousness
my counsellors: Heb. men of my counsel
So: or, So shall I answer him that reproveth me in a thing
unto: Heb. to generation and generation
they: Heb. it is ever with me
as thou: Heb. according to the custom toward those, etc
and I: or, that I may keep
Thy word: Heb. The beginning of thy word is true
nothing: Heb. they shall have no stumblingblock
